description: On Sunday, Pakistani President Arif Alvi dissolved the Pakistani parliament following Khan's advice. Imran Khan made the proposal minutes after parliament's deputy speaker rejected a motion of no confidence in him as "unconstitutional". The decision to cancel the no-confidence vote angered opposition parties and they have appealed the decision in court.
